"a quarter of a mile to the railway viaduct, and as far beyond it, till on the left, at the further side of a cottage and black barn combined, you find the rude stile of a field-path. Take this path alongside the right-hand hedge in the first field, on to a stile in the second, and te the right-hand corner of the third. On emerging there into a road, bear to the left for a quarter of a mile, till, where the road bends to the left, leaving a green corner on the right, you find the stile of a foot-path beside a field-gate. Take this path to its outlet, and tura"